+# Software Test Description (STD)
+
+## Feature: CPU Hotplug Logic Exceeding Maximum Limits
+
+**STP Reference:** [stps/6.md](/home/fedora/thesis/stps/6.md)
+**Jira ID:** [CNV-61263](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-61263)
+**Bug Fix:** [CNV-57352](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-57352)
+**PR:** [kubevirt/kubevirt#14511](https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/pull/14511)
+**Generated:** 2026-02-22
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+This STD covers tests for the CPU hotplug MaxSockets limiting fix (CNV-57352). The fix ensures that `MaxSockets` is capped so that the total vCPU count (`sockets x cores x threads`) does not exceed 512. Prior to this fix, CPU hotplug could allow exceeding the maximum vCPU limit, causing unpredictable VM behavior. The tests verify that MaxSockets is properly calculated and limited, that hotplug operations respect the limit, that appropriate errors are raised when attempting to exceed it, and that a full hotplug cycle works correctly within the enforced boundaries.
+
+---
+
+## Test Files
+
+### File: `tests/virt/node/hotplug/test_cpu_hotplug_max_limits.py`
+
+```python
+"""
+CPU Hotplug MaxSockets Limit Tests
+
+STP Reference: stps/6.md
+Jira: https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-61263
+Bug Fix: https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-57352
+PR: https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/pull/14511
+
+This module contains tests verifying that MaxSockets is properly limited
+based on the maximum allowed vCPUs (512 ceiling) when CPU hotplug is enabled.
+The fix caps MaxSockets so that sockets x cores x threads does not exceed
+the defaultMaxSocketsLimit (128 x hotplug ratio).
+"""
+
+import pytest
+
+pytestmark = pytest.mark.rwx_default_storage
+
+
+class TestCPUHotplugMaxSocketsLimit:
+    """
+    Tests for CPU hotplug MaxSockets limiting behavior.
+
+    Validates that MaxSockets is properly calculated and enforced to prevent
+    total vCPU count from exceeding the maximum allowed limit (512 vCPUs).
+
+    Markers:
+        - rwx_default_storage
+        - s390x
+
+    Preconditions:
+        - Running RHEL VM with CPU hotplug enabled
+        - VM created with cpu_max_sockets set to a value that would exceed the vCPU limit
+    """
+
+    def test_max_sockets_limited_by_vcpu_ceiling(self):
+        """
+        Test that MaxSockets is automatically capped so total vCPUs do not exceed the limit.
+
+        Preconditions:
+            - VM created with CPU hotplug enabled and a high cpu_max_sockets value
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Inspect the VMI spec to read the effective MaxSockets value
+
+        Expected:
+            - MaxSockets multiplied by cores and threads is less than or equal to 512
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_hotplug_cpu_up_to_max_sockets(self):
+        """
+        Test that CPU hotplug succeeds when target sockets are within the MaxSockets limit.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Hotplug CPU sockets to a value within the MaxSockets limit
+            2. Wait for guest OS to recognize the new CPU count
+
+        Expected:
+            - Guest OS CPU count equals the hotplugged socket value
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_hotplug_cpu_beyond_max_sockets_rejected(self):
+        """
+        [NEGATIVE] Test that CPU hotplug is rejected when target sockets exceed MaxSockets.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Attempt to hotplug CPU sockets to a value exceeding MaxSockets
+
+        Expected:
+            - UnprocessibleEntityError is raised
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_full_hotplug_cycle_within_limits(self):
+        """
+        Test that a full CPU hotplug cycle works correctly within the MaxSockets boundary.
+
+        Preconditions:
+            - VM started with initial CPU sockets below MaxSockets
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Hotplug CPU sockets incrementally up to MaxSockets
+            2. Wait for guest OS to recognize all hotplugged CPUs
+            3. Attempt to hotplug one socket beyond MaxSockets
+
+        Expected:
+            - Guest OS CPU count equals MaxSockets after hotplug
+        """
+        pass
+```
+
